cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "LeaderSpeech: Tools for scraping, transcribing, cleaning, and structuring speeches by national leaders"
abstract: >-
  A config-driven toolkit for building a comprehensive, wide-coverage dataset of national
  leaders' speeches: a recipe-based web scraper, a video/audio scraper with Whisper
  transcription, an LLM metadata-cleaning and structuring step, a translation step, and a
  leader-tenure curation loop.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Schafer
    given-names: Dean
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6774-3755"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-07-13   # TODO: set to the date of the release/tag you are citing
license: GPL-3.0-or-later
url: "https://github.com/d-schafer/LeaderSpeech"
repository-code: "https://github.com/d-schafer/LeaderSpeech"
keywords:
  - web-scraping
  - political-speech
  - nlp
  - comparative-politics

